-- Real Madrid Defeats Barcelona for Second Time in Five Days
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-03-02T17:54:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-02/real-madrid-defeats-barcelona-for-second-time-in-five-days.html
Real Madrid defeated Barcelona for
the second time in five days, as  Sergio Ramos ’s goal in the 81st
minute handed the Spanish soccer leader a 2-1 loss.  Karim Benzema also scored for Madrid, which beat Barcelona
3-1 in the semifinals of the Copa del Rey on Feb. 26.  Lionel
Messi  scored in his 16th straight La Liga match for Barcelona.
It was his 18th goal in the matchup known as “El Classico” to
tie the record set by Madrid’s Alfredo di Stefano.  Barcelona is still 12 points ahead second-place Atletico
Madrid, which plays Malaga tomorrow, while Real Madrid moved to
within 13 points of the league leader.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  